Ask HN: Kernel Level Garbage Collector
text:
I see that more and more programming languages can be AOT compiled into native code and are garbage collected. Examples: Go, C#/.NET, Nim, Java.

I wonder if implementing a garbage collector at system level in the kernel an letting those languages using that instead of each providing its own garbage collector might result in better performance.

Ask HN: Bootstrapping a remote team in different timezones, looking for tips
text:
About to hire a full time remote team and I am trying to workout how to best approach things such as a daily standup and naturing a strong sense of union and bonding. I am not completely sold on there is one way to do it, I just don't want folks to end up becoming secluded and cut-off (for both their mental health and also ensuring we all support each others efforts).

We will of course have async tools in place; slack , google hangouts etc and our development model will support a remote team (CI, Kanban, document everything).

We might have folks in Europe and Seattle, so as some individuals go offline others will start. If we hire in Asia this will add even more of a further reach.
